ZH:请赐我力量来完成这项任务。
EN: Please grant me the strength to complete this task.

ZH:他赐给我一本书作为生日礼物。
EN: He gave me a book as a birthday gift.

ZH:上帝赐予我们温暖的太阳和清新的空气。
EN: God grants us the warm sun and fresh air.

ZH:这位善良的老人赐给了我一袋食物。
EN: The kind old man bestowed me with a bag of food.

ZH:总统赐予他荣誉勋章以表彰他的贡献。
EN: The president conferred a medal upon him to honor his contributions.

ZH:父母赐予子女忠告和指导。
EN: Parents give their children advice and guidance.

ZH:这个国家赐予了市民一些权利和自由。
EN: This country grants its citizens certain rights and freedoms.

ZH:老师赐予学生一些额外的时间来完成作业。
EN: The teacher gave the students some extra time to complete their homework.

ZH:公司赐予员工一份感恩节礼物。
EN: The company bestowed Thanksgiving gifts upon its employees.

ZH:这家慈善机构赐予需要帮助的人们食物和住所。
EN: This charity organization grants food and shelter to those in need.

ZH:赐予爱与希望
EN: Grant love and hope

ZH:掌声是对艺术家们的最大赐予。
EN: Applause is the greatest gift to the artists.

ZH:祖国赐予了我们幸福的生活。
EN: Our motherland grants us a happy life.

ZH:这位慷慨的慈善家赐予了学校新的图书馆。
EN: The generous philanthropist bestowed a new library upon the school.

ZH:请赐予我一个机会证明自己。
EN: Please grant me a chance to prove myself.

ZH:父亲赐与儿子一条金链作为毕业礼物。
EN: The father bestowed a gold chain upon his son as a graduation gift.

ZH:公司赐予员工假期以感谢他们的辛勤工作。
EN: The company granted its employees a holiday to thank them for their hard work.

ZH:爱是我们共同的赐予。
EN: Love is our common bestowment.

ZH:我感到内心有一种赐予的冲动。
EN: I feel an impulse to give from my heart.

ZH:这次旅行给我们赐予了许多美好的回忆。
EN: This trip granted us many beautiful memories.
